classification.name: C3PR
classification.preferredDefinition: Version 2.8 The Cancer Central Clinical Participent Registry (C3PR) is a web-based application used to manage participants in cancer clinical trials. Research staff will use C3PR as a participant-centric entry point to clinical trial management systems. C3PR provides a central registry for study participants, and it enables the end-user to access participant-centric information that is stored in multiple clinical trial systems. A carcinoma arising from squamous epithelial cells. Morphologically, it is characterized by the proliferation of atypical, often pleomorphic squamous cells. Squamous cell carcinomas are graded by the degree of cellular differentiation as well, moderately, or poorly differentiated. Well differentiated carcinomas are usually associated with keratin production and the presence of intercellular bridges between adjacent cells.
